# Modal Implementation Pattern

**CRITICAL: Always use the Modal components from `@/components/ui/modal`, NOT Dialog components.**

## 1. Register the Modal

In `src/hooks/use-modal.tsx`, add your key and slug to `MODALS`:

```ts
export const MODALS = {
  // …existing entries
  your_new_modal: "your-new-modal"
};
```

## 2. Create the Modal Component

**ALWAYS use the Modal component structure:**

```tsx
import {
  ModalRoot,
  ModalContent,
  ModalHeader,
  ModalTitle,
  ModalDescription, // Optional
  ModalBody,
  ModalFooter, // Optional, only if you have footer actions
} from "@/components/ui/modal";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

type Props = {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
  // Add other props as needed
};

export const YourNewModal = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  return (
    <ModalRoot open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <ModalContent size="md"> {/* Use: "sm" | "md" | "lg" | "xl" | "full" */}
        <ModalHeader>
          <ModalTitle>Your Modal Title</ModalTitle>
          {/* Optional description */}
          <ModalDescription>
            Optional description text here
          </ModalDescription>
        </ModalHeader>

        <ModalBody>
          {/* Your modal content here */}
        </ModalBody>

        {/* Optional footer - only include if you have action buttons */}
        <ModalFooter>
          {/* Footer content with buttons */}
        </ModalFooter>
      </ModalContent>
    </ModalRoot>
  );
};

export default YourNewModal;
```

**For modals WITH data:**

```tsx
import {
  ModalRoot,
  ModalContent,
  ModalHeader,
  ModalTitle,
  ModalBody,
  ModalFooter,
} from "@/components/ui/modal";
import { useModals } from "@/hooks/use-modal";

type Props = {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
};

export const YourNewModal = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  const { your_new_modal } = useModals();
  const modalData = your_new_modal.data;

  return (
    <ModalRoot open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <ModalContent size="md">
        <ModalHeader>
          <ModalTitle>Your Modal Title</ModalTitle>
        </ModalHeader>

        <ModalBody>
          {/* Access modal data via `modalData` */}
          {modalData && <div>Received: {JSON.stringify(modalData)}</div>}
        </ModalBody>
      </ModalContent>
    </ModalRoot>
  );
};

export default YourNewModal;
```

## 3. Button Styling in Modals

**ALWAYS use these button props and styling in modals:**

### Button Variants (in order of usage frequency):
- `variant="primary"` - Primary action buttons (Submit, Save, Confirm, etc.)
- `variant="outlined"` - Secondary actions (Cancel, Back, Download, etc.)
- `variant="secondary"` - Alternative secondary styling
- `variant="text"` - Text-only buttons for less prominent actions

### Button Sizes:
- `size="md"` - **DEFAULT and most common** - Use for most modal buttons
- `size="lg"` - For prominent primary actions when needed
- `size="sm"` - For compact spaces or less important actions

### Standard Button Pattern:

```tsx
<ModalFooter>
  {/* Left side - Cancel/Back buttons */}
  <Button
    variant="outlined"
    size="md"
    onClick={handleCancel}
    disabled={isPending}
    type="button"
  >
    Cancel
  </Button>

  {/* Right side - Primary action */}
  <div className="flex items-center gap-4">
    <Button
      variant="primary"
      size="md"
      onClick={handleSubmit}
      disabled={isPending}
      loading={isPending} // Use loading prop for async actions
      type="button" // Always use type="button" unless it's a form submit
    >
      Submit
    </Button>
  </div>
</ModalFooter>
```

### Footer Layout Patterns:

**Pattern 1: Justified (Back on left, Primary on right)**
```tsx
<ModalFooter className="justify-between">
  <Button variant="outlined" size="md" onClick={onClose}>
    Back
  </Button>
  <Button variant="primary" size="md" onClick={onSubmit}>
    Next
  </Button>
</ModalFooter>
```

**Pattern 2: Centered actions**
```tsx
<ModalFooter>
  <div className="flex gap-3 w-full justify-center">
    <Button variant="outlined" size="md" onClick={action1}>
      Action 1
    </Button>
    <Button variant="outlined" size="md" onClick={action2}>
      Action 2
    </Button>
  </div>
</ModalFooter>
```

**Pattern 3: Right-aligned actions**
```tsx
<ModalFooter>
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2 ml-auto">
    <Button variant="outlined" size="md" onClick={onCancel}>
      Cancel
    </Button>
    <Button variant="primary" size="md" onClick={onSubmit}>
      Save
    </Button>
  </div>
</ModalFooter>
```

### Button with Icons:

```tsx
<Button
  variant="outlined"
  size="md"
  onClick={handleAction}
  className="flex gap-2" // Add gap for icon spacing
>
  <DownloadSimple size={16} /> {/* Icon size: 16 for md buttons */}
  Download
</Button>
```

## 4. Wire it up

In the layout or page where the modal belongs:

```tsx
import { useModals } from "@/hooks/use-modal";
import YourNewModal from "@/components/modals/your-new-modal";

const SomePage = () => {
  const { your_new_modal } = useModals();

  return (
    <>
      {/* …other content… */}

      <YourNewModal open={your_new_modal.state} onOpenChange={your_new_modal.toggle} />
    </>
  );
};
```

## 5. Opening & Closing Modals

   **Basic usage (no data):**

   ```ts
   const { your_new_modal } = useModals();
   your_new_modal.toggle(true); // open
   your_new_modal.toggle(false); // close
   ```

   **With data passing:**

   ```ts
   const { your_new_modal } = useModals();

   // Open with data
   your_new_modal.toggle(true, {
     data: { userId: 123, name: "John" }
   });

   // Set data without opening
   your_new_modal.setData({ userId: 456 });

   // Access current data
   console.log(your_new_modal.data);

   // Clear data
   your_new_modal.clearData();
   ```

   **Using the convenience hook:**

   ```ts
   import { useModalWithData } from "@/hooks/use-modal";

   const { openWithData, close, data } = useModalWithData("your_new_modal");

   // Open with data
   openWithData({ userId: 123, response: apiResponse });

   // Close modal
   close();
   ```

## 6. Data Management

- Data is automatically stored in localStorage with key `modal_data_{modal-name}`
- Data is automatically cleared when modal closes
- Data persists across page refreshes while modal is open
- Data is automatically cleaned up when switching between modals

## 7. Complete Example

Here's a complete example following all conventions:

```tsx
import { useState } from "react";
import {
  ModalRoot,
  ModalContent,
  ModalHeader,
  ModalTitle,
  ModalBody,
  ModalFooter,
} from "@/components/ui/modal";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Input } from "@/components/ui/input";
import { useToast } from "@/components/ui/use-toast";

type Props = {
  open: boolean;
  onOpenChange: (open: boolean) => void;
};

export const ExampleModal = ({ open, onOpenChange }: Props) => {
  const { toast } = useToast();
  const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);

  const handleSubmit = async () => {
    setIsLoading(true);
    // Your async logic here
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
    setIsLoading(false);
    toast({ title: "Success!" });
    onOpenChange(false);
  };

  return (
    <ModalRoot open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
      <ModalContent size="md">
        <ModalHeader>
          <ModalTitle>Example Modal</ModalTitle>
        </ModalHeader>

        <ModalBody>
          <div className="flex flex-col gap-4">
            <Input placeholder="Enter value..." />
            {/* Your form content here */}
          </div>
        </ModalBody>

        <ModalFooter className="justify-between">
          <Button
            variant="outlined"
            size="md"
            onClick={() => onOpenChange(false)}
            disabled={isLoading}
            type="button"
          >
            Cancel
          </Button>

          <Button
            variant="primary"
            size="md"
            onClick={handleSubmit}
            disabled={isLoading}
            loading={isLoading}
            type="button"
          >
            Submit
          </Button>
        </ModalFooter>
      </ModalContent>
    </ModalRoot>
  );
};

export default ExampleModal;
```

## Key Rules Summary

✅ **ALWAYS:**
- Use `ModalRoot`, `ModalContent`, `ModalHeader`, `ModalTitle`, `ModalBody`, `ModalFooter` from `@/components/ui/modal`
- Use `size="md"` for ModalContent (default)
- Use `variant="outlined"` and `size="md"` for secondary buttons
- Use `variant="primary"` and `size="md"` for primary action buttons
- Include `type="button"` on buttons unless it's a form submit
- Use `loading` prop for async button states
- Use `disabled` prop when action is not available

❌ **NEVER:**
- Use `Dialog` or `DialogContent` components
- Use `variant="outline"` (use `variant="outlined"` instead)
- Omit button size prop (always specify `size="md"` or appropriate size)
- Use inline styles for buttons (use variant and size props)
